Typical request flow (in English)

Client POST /ingest/upload with metadata + file.

Service validates the user.

Writes the uploaded file to a temp location.

Copies RAW to storage, remembers rawUri.

Extracts plain text to another temp file.

Copies TXT to storage, remembers textUri.

Reads TXT, computes SHA-256 + character count.

Inserts book row with status TEXT_READY.

Returns the bookId (as string).

If anything fails, you log + wrap the error; temp files stay on disk for now.